    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare(java.lang.Object o1,
                   java.lang.Object o2)
        compare() is a method used to compare the distance of two Shape objects. If the distance of the shape being compared to is less it returns a 1, if it is more it returns a -1 and it returns a 0 if the volume is equal. This interface allows the Arrays.sort() method to sort the shapes in descending order based on how far the center of the object is from origin.
        Specified by:
        compare in interface java.util.Comparator
        Parameters:
        o1 - is a Shape object to compare.
        o2 - is a Shape object to compare against.
        Returns:
        1 ,-1 or 0 to signify if the volume is less, more or equal.
